title: Fair Isaac: Fiscal 2Q Earnings Snapshot
text:
SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) _ Fair Isaac Corp. (FICO) on Thursday reported fiscal second-quarter earnings of $32.3 million.
The San Jose, California-based company said it had net income of $1.03 per share. Earnings, adjusted for one-time gains and costs, were $1.54 per share.
The financial services company posted revenue of $257.9 million in the period.
Fair Isaac expects full-year earnings to be $6.38 per share, with revenue expected to be $1.02 billion.
Fair Isaac shares have climbed 11 percent since the beginning of the year. The stock has increased 28 percent in the last 12 months.
